#Download the .zip   https://dl.google.com/android/repository/platform-tools-latest-linux.zip
#Open the Terminal and enter the command $sudo apt-get install android-tools-adb
#Open the Android device and follow these steps 
1. Go to the Settings
2. Tap About Phone
3. Press the Build Number 7 times
4.Enter the PIN code
5.The Developer options menu will appear in Settings menu
6.Enter the Developer Options section
7.Enable USB Debugging 
#Connect your device to a Linux computer using USB cable
#A request will appear on the smartphone asking you to allow USB debugging. Grant it.
#Enter the command in the Terminal    $adb devices 
#Make a device screen using           $adb shell screencap -p /sdcard/screen.png 
#Get a photo                          $adb pull /sdcard/screen.png 
#Record the device screen with        $adb shell screenrecord /sdcard/demo.mp4 AND stop it with ^C
                           OR         $adb shell screenrecord --time-limit=120 /mnt/sdcard/demo.mp4
#Get the video                        $adb pull /sdcard/demo.mp4
#Do logcat                            $adb logcat
